        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 3:03AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 303 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Glen Wilton to near Oriskany to near Sinking
Creek. Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Troutville...
New Castle...
Catawba...
Eagle Rock...
Oriskany...
Collierstown...
and Iron Gate.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM EDT for
southwestern Virginia...and southeastern West Virginia.</instruction>
